.TH M33MU 1 "" "m33mu" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
m33mu \- Cortex-M33 emulator
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B m33mu
.RI [ options ]
.IR image.bin [:offset]
.RI [ image.bin[:offset] ...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
m33mu emulates ARMv8-M Cortex-M targets with TrustZone awareness.
It can load one or more images into flash. Raw binaries may include a byte
offset suffix (hex supported). ELF and Intel HEX images are auto-detected and
scattered into flash by their load addresses.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR --cpu " " <cpu>
Select the CPU profile (default: stm32h563).
.TP
.BR --gdb
Start the GDB remote server (RSP) on port 1234.
.TP
.BR --port " " <n>
Set the GDB server port (1-65535).
.TP
.BR --gdb-symbols " " <elf>
Load symbols from the specified ELF. Can be specified multiple times; user-provided ELFs take priority over auto-detected ones.
.TP
.BR --dump
Print per-instruction decode and selected TrustZone transitions.
.TP
.BR --tui
Start the interactive terminal UI.
.TP
.BR --record
Enable in-memory execution trace for reverse stepping.
.TP
.BR --call-trace
Log call/return, interrupt, and TrustZone SG transitions with symbol names when available.
.TP
.BR --expect-bkpt " " NN
Exit with code 0 only if a BKPT with the given immediate (hex) is hit.
.TP
.BR --fault-clock " " NNN
Skip execution of the instruction fetched when the virtual cycle counter reaches NNN. May be specified multiple times (up to 16), but values cannot be contiguous. Used to emulate "fault injection" attacks, to skip single instructions (based on clock time).
.TP
.BR --timeout " " seconds
Exit with code 127 if the host timeout elapses (SIGALRM).
.TP
.BR --persist
Write modified flash contents back to the input image files.
.TP
.BR --capstone
Enable Capstone-based cross-check logging for decode/execute.
.TP
.BR --capstone-verbose
Include operand cross-check details in Capstone logs.
.TP
.BR --uart-stdout
Route UART output to stdout instead of a PTY device.
.TP
.BR --quit-on-faults
Stop execution after the first fault is raised.
.TP
.BR --dualbank
Enable dual-bank flash mode for STM32 targets (allows runtime bank swap).
.TP
.BR --meminfo
Emit SAU/MPU layout and register write logs.
.TP
.BR --no-tz
Force non-secure boot and disable TrustZone protections for the session.
.TP
.BR --spiflash:SPIx:file=PATH:size=N[:mmap=ADDR][:cs=GPIONAME]
Attach a SPI flash image.
.TP
.BR --usb
Enable USB/IP backend (default port 3240).
.TP
.BR --usb:port= N
Enable USB/IP backend and set port.
.TP
.BR --tap[:tap0]
Enable Ethernet TAP backend (default interface: tap0).
.TP
.BR --vde[:/var/run/vde.ctl]
Enable Ethernet VDE backend (default socket: /var/run/vde.ctl).
.TP
.BR --tpm:SPIx:cs=GPIONAME[:file=PATH]
Attach a TPM TIS device (optional NV backing file).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B CAPSTONE_PC
Limit Capstone cross-check logging to a specific PC (hex).
.TP
.B M33MU_STRCMP_TRACE
Trace strcmp-like loops over a PC range (hex start:end).
.TP
.B M33MU_STRCMP_ENTRY
Override the entry PC for strcmp tracing (hex).
.TP
.B M33MU_MEMWATCH
Watch a memory range (hex addr:size).
.TP
.B M33MU_NVIC_TRACE
Trace NVIC state changes when set to 1.
.TP
.B M33MU_SYSTICK_TRACE
Trace SysTick register access and tick behavior when set to 1.
.TP
.B M33MU_SLEEP_TRACE
Trace WFE/WFI sleep and wake decisions when set to 1.
.TP
.B M33MU_PROT_TRACE
Print SAU/MPU attribution decisions (1-3 for verbosity).
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B m33mu tests/firmware/test-stm32h563/app.bin
Run a basic STM32H563 firmware test.
.TP
.B m33mu --tap tests/firmware/test-stm32h563/app.bin
Run with Ethernet TAP backend.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR gdb (1)
